Hi Agaming+, I wanted to express my gratitude for attempting to bring a game just like S.T.A.L.K.E.R to the mobile platform, and would like to congratulate you for a successful release.  I do however, think that there are many improvements that could be made in many areas and would like to give you insight to help this game reach its potential. Here is a list of problems that should be worked on in no order:  1. Translation: the English translation is really broken and jarring. The sentences make sense but only after trying to put together the broken words.  If you would like, I could make the dialogue spotless and able to convey the messages that are trying to be communicated, and I can do so for free.  2. Price: for a project this big, the price should be at least doubled. As a consumer, I have seen many games that have half of the content you are offering, but cost 2 or 3 times as much.  If you are going to make a game like this, you should be getting the compensation you need to make it the best it can be while also being compensated for your time.   3. Animations: the animations as a whole need to be worked on, ESPECIALLY on the way humans walk or run, it looks jarring and unnatural.  The animations for monsters seem to be really fast which makes them look very strange.  4. AI: when you are shot at by an enemy, it appears as though their rate of fire is increased to the point to where it seems they are using chainguns.  Also, enemies tend to focus mainly on you even when being attacked by others. Why a man would continue shooting at me despite being attacked by 2 or 3 ghouls makes no sense. Human enemies should attempt to find cover instead of rushing you and standing in the open  5. UI: being able to change the colors of the on screen buttons would be very helpful as they are rather hard to see for a first time player. The ability to resize and remove icons would also be good to have as i see no need for some.  6. Settings / options: an audio setting tab is absolutely needed. The looking sensitivity needs to be able to go higher while also having a separate slider for aiming. A simple preset graphics option with an FPS counter ranging from low to high that is accessible from the in game menu would be very helpful in players being able to determine what their device can handle.  7. Maps: the maps absolutely NEED those radiation zones removed. Not only do they force you to move in a very linear way, but they also take up way too much space. They should be replaced with more NPC spawns as there is a real lack of hostile or friendly interaction that most open world video games have to offer. Of course also, much bigger maps filled with loot, buildings, enemies, friendlies, and whatever else you think would be a nice addition.  8. Guns, ammo, and bartering:  the guns need to be able to have a select fire switch as ammo is hard to come by at certain times and WAY more expensive than it should be. I believe you may be going for the "ammo is money now" approach, but that simply does not work in a game where shooting is a priority. Everything should cost less and the player should not get as much money for doing things and instead get more items like in the STALKER games.  Enemy weapons should not be broken all the time, as selling or using the weapons of fallen enemies has always been an essential step in any kind of RPG. As of now, to get 50 rounds of assault rifle ammunition, you would have to sell multiple rifles amd other things, and if you don't get back the ammunition you used on them, then your supply will start to dwindle until you reach the situation i have found myself in time and time again of no way to defend myself.  These are just a few areas i see that need improvement as of now, and i will continue to add as I play more. If you need help with the English translation, just ask and i will be happy to.
replyContent:
Hi! Yes, English translation is made by our programmer who is not translator nor native English speaker ;)
So it might be pretty far from perfect. If you wish to help the project we will be glad. Please write to aliorunity@gmail.com to be able to discuss all that. About other topics you mentioned - you are right in most of them. Thanks!
